al production.” Their current priority is to be a hub for resources including land tenure models, legal considerations, and contract agreements. They act as a partner to FarmLINK, who links up new farmers with farm owners offering land and mentorship through an online MatchMaker tool.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:30','2013-06-17 09:26:30',8,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(150,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Landshare','','','','http://landsharecanada.com/','http://www.facebook.com/LandshareCanada','https://twitter.com/LandshareCa','Based off a model from the UK, Landshare Canada is a nation-wide database to find listings and map tools for land to be shared and make a profile that land owners can browse. Be sure to check out the easy tutorials on how to use the  landsharing tools. They also have uploaded useful sample agreements and case studies.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:30','2013-06-17 09:26:30',8,'Web',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(151,49.1705,-123.183,NULL,'100-3675 Westminster Hwy Richmond, BC V7C 5V0','Richmond Food Security Society','','Lower Mainland','','www.richmondfoodsecurity.org/','http://www.facebook.com/richmondfood','','This organization hosts a yardshare map for people to either list land to share or land wanted. Interested in a small growing space? Sign-up on the waitlist for a community garden plot in one of Richmond\'s 7 gardens. Interested in a larger growing space? Contact RFSS for more information on their Richmond incubator farm project for new farmers.  As well, the launched in 2013 an Educational Garden Plot Program, which provides access to a community garden plot alongside guidance from a Master Gardener.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:30','2013-06-17 09:26:30',8,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(152,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Sharing Backyards','','','','http://sharingbackyards.com/','','','Run as an initiative of the Lifecycles Project Society, Sharing Backyards provides a simple yet highly effective model for communities to increase the food produced in urban spaces. Those wanting to grow a garden  but lack the space can seach through the listings of available yards or create an ad for yard owners to browse. Through their website, users can browse the cities where SB projects already exist, or be given the tools and support to start their own.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:31','2013-06-17 09:26:31',8,'Web',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(153,50.2653,-119.271,NULL,'202 3002 32nd Ave, Vernon BC Canada V1T 2L7','Certified Organic Association of BC','','Thompson-Okanagan','','http://www.certifiedorganic.bc.ca/','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Certified-Organic-Associations-of-BC/208548192519986','','This is an umbrella organization for all the organic certifying bodies in BC.  They help promote organics and have services for farmers including CyberHelp and a yearly conference.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:31','2013-09-16 00:53:40',9,'Location','','',NULL,NULL,'Vernon','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(154,NULL,NULL,NULL,'','Worldwide Opporunities on Organic Farms (Woof)','','','','www.wwoof.org','http://www.facebook.com/WWOOF','https://twitter.com/WWOOF','A website that offers Information exchange for volunteer workers and the organic WWOOF host farms who offer a learning and working opportunity. WWOOFing is a great opportunity to try out different farms and locales for shorter periods of time. A small fee applies for accessing their list of available farms.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:31','2013-06-17 09:26:31',9,'Web',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(155,43.6881,-79.3938,NULL,'Across Canada','Rainbow Chard Collective','','','','http://rainbowchardcollective.wordpress.com/','https://www.facebook.com/rainbowchardcalendar','','This collective organizes to raise the visibility and networking of queer farmers in BC, and members primarily located in the lower mainland and Vancouver Island. Past initiatives have including farmer mixers, film screening, pride parade and panel discussions. Oh, and their calendar is a must for those who appreciate a well-developed farmer tan.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:31','2013-06-17 09:26:31',9,'Web',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(156,49.2712,-123.136,NULL,'Suite 203, 1661 Duranleau Street\nNet Loft, Granville Island,\nVancouver, BC V6H 3S3','BC Seeds','','Lower Mainland','','http://www.bcseeds.org/','','','BC Seeds, a project of FarmFolk City Folk, is a collective of BC seed producers and seed sovereignty advocates who are working to grow and disseminate locally-adapted, robust, non-GMO seed to the regions in BC. Recent achievements include collaboration on the Bauta Initiative on Canadian Seed Security, the hosting of numerous workshops and the first annual BC Seeds Gathering in November 2012, bringing together seed growers, farmers, advocates and seed enthusiasts to learn, share, access seed cleaning equipment and inspire seed sovereignty in the region. . Their website offers seed-growing resources and reports, links to projects and information on upcoming events.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:31','2013-09-16 00:34:46',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Vancouver','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(157,49.2855,-123.114,NULL,'Suite 1056,\n409 Granville Street,\nVancouver BC, V6C 1T2','Community Futures British Columbia','','Lower Mainland','','http://www.communityfutures.ca/index.html','http://www.facebook.com/CommunityFuturesBritishColumbia','https://twitter.com/Comm_FuturesBC','Community Futures was established by the federal government to address economic uncertainy for rural communities in BC by providing entrepreneurial and community development. 34 locations are listed on the website along with a tool matching up rural communities with their nearest location. The initiative provides small business loans up to $150 000 with flexible repayment schedules, as well as self-empoyment program for those currently or recently on EI. Participants in the self-employment program can receive business training and access to financial assistance. Check website for eligibility and details.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:31','2013-09-16 00:34:45',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Vancouver','CA','CA','BC','BC'),(158,48.7259,-123.698,NULL,'2881 Mountain Road, Duncan, BC, V9L 6N4','BC Sheep Federation','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','','http://www.bcsheepfed.com','http://www.facebook.com/BarbBCSF','','An organization devoted to promoting a  profitable, connected and thriving sheep and wool industry in BC. Membership runs at $20/year, and provides online advertising via the federation\'s \'Buyer\'s Guide\', as well as representation provincially and federally on issues affecting sheep farmers. The website also lists events and publications.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:32','2013-06-17 09:26:32',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(159,50.6687,-120.185,NULL,'#4-10145 Dallas Drive Kamloops, BC V2C 6T4','BC Cattlemen\'s Association','','Thompson-Okanagan','','http://www.cattlemen.bc.ca/','','','An association representing over 1200 cattle ranchers in BC and many regional and local associations. Check out their website for fact sheets in the \'Resource\' section and for more information on their various programs geared to improve cattle ranch operations.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:32','2013-06-17 09:26:32',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(160,56.2472,-120.851,NULL,'V1J 4H6','BC Grain Producers Association','','Northeast','','http://www.bcgrain.com','','','BC Grain Producers represents the interest of grain growers in BC. Their work is focused on making grain and oilseed production in the BC Peace River region economically viable.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:32','2013-09-16 00:54:11',9,'Location','','',NULL,NULL,'Fort St John','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(161,49.2635,-123.128,NULL,'103 – 1089 West Broadway Vancouver, BC V6H 1E5','BC Farmers Market Association','','Lower Mainland','','http://www.bcfarmersmarket.org/','','https://twitter.com/BCFarmersMarket','This organization is committed to a vibrant farmers\' market culture in BC. Their website contains helpful resources on insurance and health regulations at markets, as well as a search engine for locating farmers\' markets in your area.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:32','2013-09-16 00:54:11',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Vancouver','CA','CA','BC','BC'),(162,49.8873,-119.497,NULL,'1473 Water Street Kelowna, BC V1Y 1J6','BC Fruit Growers Association','','Thompson-Okanagan','','http://www.bcfga.com/','http://www.facebook.com/pages/BC-Fruit-Growers-Association/208331935875260','','An association representing the interests of the BC fruit growers to government, industry and the public. Use their website to learn about news and events in the BC fruit growing world, as well as intitiatives on topics such as integrated pest management, water and environment.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:32','2013-09-16 00:54:12',9,'Location','','',NULL,NULL,'Kelowna','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(163,49.83,-124.523,NULL,'6916 Invermere Court Powell River, BC V8A 1N5','BC Food Systems Network','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','','fooddemocracy.org/','http://www.facebook.com/BCFSN','','Across BC, the BCFSN facilitates collaboration on sustainable and just food systems at the community level. They engage and support policy analysis of local food systems and hold an annual grassroots gathering to celebrate food, farmers and land. This provincial organization operates over a dozen active listservs.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:33','2013-09-16 00:34:43',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Powell River','CA','CA','BC','BC'),(164,48.4931,-123.389,NULL,'203-4475 Viewmont Avenue Victoria, BC V8Z 6L8','Capital Region Food and Agriculture Initatives Round Table','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','','http://www.communitycouncil.ca/initiatives/crfair/','','','CR-FAIR is a coalition of organizations and individuals that work to bolster regional food secuirty and the relocalization of Southern Vancouver Island\'s food system through policy, community building and working group initiatives. They hosted the Farmer2Farmer conference in 2013 to bring together local producers to share knowledge on local topics.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:33','2013-06-17 09:26:33',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(165,49.2712,-123.136,NULL,'Suite 203, 1661 Duranleau Street Net Loft, Granville Island, Vancouver, BC V6H 3S3','FarmFolk CityFolk','','Lower Mainland','','http://www.farmfolkcityfolk.ca','http://www.facebook.com/FarmFolkCityFolk','https://twitter.com/FFCF','A non-profit organization that coordinates projects that benefit farmers and the local food sector. FFCF has worked on numerous campaigns on the protection of farmland, alternative and community farm models and creating celebration around sharing food. Current farm projects include a micro-loan fund, Young Agrarians, Community Farms, BC Seeds and Grain Chain.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:33','2013-09-16 00:53:31',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Vancouver','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(166,45.5112,-73.5776,NULL,'3720 Parc Avenue, Suite 201 Montreal, QC H2X 2J1','Food Secure Canada','','','','http://foodsecurecanada.org','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Food-Secure-Canada/316790952902','https://twitter.com/FoodSecureCAN','Food Secure Canada is a national non-profit committed to addressing hundger, food health and safety and the sustainability of our food systems. Check out their \'People\'s Food Policy for Canada\', and browse through their volunteer, career and internship opportunities. There are different networks one can join based on interest.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:33','2013-06-17 09:26:33',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(167,43.5463,-80.2496,NULL,'P.O. Box 1875, Guelph, Ontario N1H 7A1','FarmStart Ontario','','','','http://www.farmstart.ca/','http://www.facebook.com/FarmStartBC','','An organization with a wealth of information and programs for new farmers',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:33','2013-09-16 00:49:48',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Guelph','CA','CA','ON','ON'),(168,52.1718,-106.656,NULL,'2717 Wentz Avenue, Saskatoon, Saskatchewan, S7K 4B6','National Farm Union of Canada Youth Network','','','306-652-9465','http://www.nfu.ca/about/youth','https://www.facebook.com/nfuCanada/info','https://twitter.com/NFUCanada','This powerhouse organization does extensive research and advocacy around economic and social policies that affect farmers and food sovereignty in Canada. Their activities include producing and disseminating policy statements and holding annual conventions, and they are particularly active in sounding the alarm on Canada’s Comprehensive Economic and Trade Agreement with the European Union and in opposing genetically modified crops. The Youth Network links rural and urban youth in building a just and economically viable food system. Farm youth age 14-29 can join NFU Youth through either a yearly youth membership, or full membership. The NFU is also a member of La Via Campesina, a global sustainable agriculture movement.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:34','2013-06-17 09:26:34',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(169,48.4377,-123.37,NULL,'Unit # 2 - 625 Hillside Ave.\nVictoria, BC\nV8T 1Z1','LifeCycles Project Society','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','','http://lifecyclesproject.ca/','http://www.facebook.com/pages/LifeCycles-Project-Society/202655149841805','https://twitter.com/LifeCyclesPrjct','LifeCycles is an active non-profit that initiates and facilitates community action on environmentally and socially sustainable food systems and urban ecosystems. Programs cover many topic areas in many locales- but they all seek to develop intergenerational learning, strengthen connections and foster a sense of belonging through urban agriculture. Browse their many initiatives for volunteer opportunities. Their projects focus heavily on skill-building for their volunteers and the communities they serve, from fruit pickers with the Fruit Tree Project, to elementary school-aged students with Growing Schools.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:34','2013-06-17 09:26:34',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(170,48.4294,-123.35,NULL,'1216 North Park St.\nVictoria, BC V8T 1C9','Greater Victoria Compost Education Centre','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','','http://www.compost.bc.ca/','http://www.facebook.com/CompostEducation','https://twitter.com/viccomposted','The Greater Victoria Compost Education Centre is a organic-growing hub for education on ecological gardening, conservation, local food and, of course, composting. They maintain a telephone hotline for general organic gardening and composting questions, keep up a diverse demonstration site and hold numerous public education programs, including their youth program SLUGS- Sustainable Living and Urban Gardening Skills. Through partneships with local organizations and individuals they put on a good diversity of beginner and intensive workshops.',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:34','2013-06-17 09:26:34',9,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(171,49.2812,-123.108,NULL,'517 - 119 west pender street, vancouver, bc, V6B 1S5','Environmental Youth Alliance','','Lower Mainland','','http://www.eya.ca/','http://www.facebook.com/EnvironmentalYouthAlliance','https://twitter.com/EnviroYA','The EYA is a youth-driven non-profit that delivers programs concerned with community and environmental health. Their food and farming-focused programs cover various topics- from seeds, to pollinator health, to a community nursery. There are many options to volunteer and skill-build with the EYA,',1,'2013-06-17 09:26:34','2013-08-20 17:32:45',9,'Location','','',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(172,49.2671,-123.143,NULL,'2060-B Pine Street, Vancouver, BC, V6J 4P8','The Society Promoting Environmental Conservation','','Lower Mainland','604-736-7732','http://www.spec.bc.ca/food','http://www.facebook.com/pages/Society-Promoting-Environmental-Conser