 join us at the Cherryville Farmers Market in the heart of the beautiful Monashee Mountains. Enjoy our wide variety of organic produce, farm products, fresh foods, handmade crafts and many more items which our creative and productive community has to offer. Be entertained from our live music /performance tent, while enjoying fresh whole foods from one of our many vendors.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:19','2013-07-29 18:02:19',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(493,51.6426,-120.024,NULL,'516-542 Swanson Road, Clearwater, V0E 1N1, BC','Clearwater Farmers\' Market','','Thompson-Okanagan','250-674-3444','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/clearwater-farmers-market','','','Saturdays, Summer: The Clearwater Farmers Market is having it\'s 12th anniversary this year. As with many Farmers Markets it started out with a few Vendors but has grown to as many as 26. Dedication from individuals, Vendors and the community has grown the Market into a Fun Healthy event for everyone! Entertainment is welcome in our Event Tent which showcases our local talent on many a Saturday morning. The Clearwater Farmers Market has a wide array of Vendors and Artisans selling everything from crafts to chocolates, plants, flowers, herbs, baking, seasonal fruits and lots of vegetables. Come and enjoy some of freshest food in the valley! We\'re located on the grounds of Interior Whitewater Expeditions. See you there!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:20','2013-07-29 18:02:20',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(494,49.0314,-118.446,NULL,'7248-7350 9 St, Grand Forks, V0H 1H9, BC','Grand Forks Farmer\'s Market','gffarmersmarket@hotmail.com','Thompson-Okanagan','','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/grand-forks-farmers-market','','','Tuesdays, Fridays, Summer, Fall: Located in Gyro Park on Highway 3 (accross from Overwaitea), the Grand Forks\' Farmers\' Market runs 2 times a week and boasts locally grown fruit and veggies, bedding plants, flowers, trees and shrubs, locally raised meat and eggs, handmade prepared foods made with whole, organic and vegan ingredients, hand made crafts that range from, clothing, tea, bath soaks, jewelery, pottery, knits, paintings, and so much more! Come out and join us Tuesdays and Fridays from 8am - 1pm and We look forward to seeing you there!! :)',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:20','2013-07-29 18:02:20',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(495,49.358,-120.077,NULL,'825-897 Scott Ave, Hedley, V0X 1K0, BC','Hedley Farmers Market','hedleyfarmersmarket@hotmail.com','Thompson-Okanagan','250-292-8511','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/hedley-farmers-market','https://www.facebook.com/HedleyFarmersMarket?fref=ts','','Sundays, Summer: Nestled under the backdrop of the Mascot Gold Mine on Nickelplate Mountain, our market is held every Sunday morning in Heritage Park, Hedley BC across the street from the Hedley Heritage Museum. Located between Princeton and Keremeos on Highway 3, we are the ONLY farmers market in the Similkameen Valley. We offer a variety of locally grown and locally made items from all over our beautiful valley. You will be able to buy organic, untreated and unsprayed fruit,veggies, baking and preserves. Whether you live nearby or you are traveling through, be sure to take the time to stop in Hedley for some fresh and creative goodies.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:20','2013-07-29 18:02:20',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(496,50.6743,-120.336,NULL,'236 St Paul St, Kamloops, BC V2C 6G4, Canada','Kamloops Regional Farmers\' Market','info@kamloopsfarmersmarket.com','Thompson-Okanagan','250-682-7975','http://www.kamloopsfarmersmarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/KamloopsFarmersMarket','','Wednesdays, Saturdays, Summer, Fall: The purpose of the Kamloops Regional Farmers\' Market Society is to encourage and support local production of food, and to provide an outlet for local produce and foods, in order to promote local food security.The market features a wide variety of vendors selling vegetables, fruit, meat, honey, baking, bedding plants, and flowers, as well as crafts and other home-based business products. We often have local musicians and other buskers. Come and join us for a great shopping experience in downtown Kamloops and support the local economy at the same time!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:20','2013-07-29 18:02:20',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(497,37.7838,-85.3991,NULL,'Springfield Rd & Dilworth Dr, Kelowna, BC V1W, Canada ','Kelowna Farmers and Crafters Market','kelownafarmersmarket@shaw.ca','Thompson-Okanagan','250 878-5029','http://www.kelownafarmersandcraftersmarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/kelownafarmersandcraftersmarket','','Wednesday, Saturdays, Summer, Fall: This market offers a huge variety of farm products and organic produce, jams, baking, meats, ethnic foods, soaps, body products, flowers, plants, concessions, entertainment, festivals and much, much more. You will not be disappointed!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:21','2013-07-29 18:02:21',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(498,49.8878,-119.496,NULL,'1435 Water St, Kelowna, BC V1Y, Canada','Kelowna Farmers and Crafters Market (Indoor-Winter Market)','kelownafarmersmarket@shaw.ca','Thompson-Okanagan','250 878-5029','http://www.kelownafarmersandcraftersmarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/kelownafarmersandcraftersmarket','','Saturdays, Winter, Spring: Open from first Sat. in November to last Sat. in March. Outstanding indoor winter market.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:21','2013-07-29 18:02:21',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(499,49.5991,-119.602,NULL,'3795-3855 1 St, Naramata, BC V0H 1N0, Canada','Naramata Community Market Society','naramatamarket@shaw.ca','Thompson-Okanagan','250-496-4182','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/naramata-community-market-society','','','Wednesdays, Summer, Fall: Welcome to sunny Naramata, nestled in the heart of some of BC\'s best orchards and rolling vineyards. If you share our commitment to supporting local farmers and reducing your \"food miles\", you\'ll feel right at home here in Naramata. We offer the very best of freshly harvested, seasonal, local foods in addition to exquisite locally prepared foods, such as mustards, salad dressings, chutneys and preserves. And the range of freshly baked breads and pastries has to be seen to be believed. \n',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:21','2013-07-29 18:02:21',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(500,50.1112,-120.786,NULL,'2088 Garcia St, Merritt, BC V1K 1N3, Canada','Nicola Valley Farmers\' Market','car_crazy01@hotmail.com','Thompson-Okanagan','250-378-2124','','https://www.facebook.com/nicolavalleyfarmersmarket','','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: A growing market with a mix of woodwork to baking, corn to buffalo meat. Always looking for crafters and vendors.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:21','2013-07-29 18:02:21',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(501,49.1818,-119.552,NULL,'9315 Fairview Rd, Oliver, BC V0H 1T0, Canada','Oliver Country Market','oliverfarmersmarket@gmail.com','Thompson-Okanagan','250-498-3369','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/oliver-country-market','','','Thursdays, Summer: Small country market in the midst of the sunny South Okanagan community of Oliver. We strive to encourage our customers to enjoy a \"Healthy Living/Healthy Community\" lifestyle. We have partnered in principle with the town of Oliver and have the support of the Regional District of Okanagan Similkameen to help get the word out. We provide produce, baking, honey & crafts of the highest quality at reasonable prices.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:21','2013-07-29 18:02:21',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(502,49.032,-119.465,NULL,'\n85 St, Osoyoos, BC V0H 1V0, Canada','Osoyoos Market on Main','osoyoosmarketonmain@hotmail.com','Thompson-Okanagan','','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/osoyoos-market-main','','','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: \"Home Made- Home Grown\" Local vendors provide a variety of home made and home grown items to locals and tourists in our town. We promote agritourism, entrepreneurship and local artisans. We want to promote healthy living and environmental friendliness, community interaction and participation.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:21','2013-07-29 18:02:21',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(503,49.5013,-119.594,NULL,'16-158 Main St, Penticton, BC V2A 8G7, Canada ','Penticton Farmers Market','pentictonfarmersmarket@gmail.com','Thompson-Okanagan','250 770 FARM (3276)','http://pentictonfarmersmarket.org','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Penticton-Farmers-Market/212196298810004','','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: Come Enjoy the Best Market in the Okanagan. 100 Block of Main Street in Penticton. The Freshest Fruit and Veggies you can imagine. Meet our wonderful Vendors who offer the widest variety of everything. See you at the market! New for 2012: Tuesday Farmers\' Markets will be held from 3-7pm at the Shatford Centre, 760 Main St during july and August',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:22','2013-07-29 18:02:22',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(504,50.6996,-119.29,NULL,'386 Trans-Canada Hwy, Salmon Arm, BC V1E 1E4, Canada','Shuswap Farm and Craft Market','info@shuswapfarmersmarket.com','Thompson-Okanagan','250-804-3387','http://www.shuswapfarmersmarket.com','','','Tuesdays, Fridays, Spring-Fall: Fresh farm products and local crafts—and it\'s all made, baked, or grown locally! There are about 70 regular vendors here, offering fresh fruits and veggies; delicious home baking; craftworks; woodworking; bedding plants; and more.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:22','2013-07-29 18:02:22',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(505,50.8768,-119.47,NULL,'1204 Notch Hill Rd, Sorrento, BC V0E 2W1, Canada','Sorrento Village Farmers\' Market','sorrentofarmersmarket@yahoo.ca','Thompson-Okanagan','250-515-1265','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/sorrento-village-farmers-market','','','Saturdays, Spring-Fall: The Sorrento Market is the place to be on a Shuswap Saturday morning. Fresh local organic produce, fine baked goods, eggs, cut flowers, preserves; Shuswap artisans sell their wares and local musicians entertain. ',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:22','2013-07-29 18:02:22',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(506,50.8777,-119.909,NULL,'Alpine Rd, Heffley Creek, BC V0E 1Z1, Canada','Sun Peaks & Region Farmers\' Market','addventuresupervisor@sunpeakstourism.com','Thompson-Okanagan','250-578-5388','http://www.sunpeaksresort.com/farmers-market','https://www.facebook.com/SunPeaksResort','','Sundays, Summer: This is an opportunity for guests and locals to purchase fruits and veggies from local farmers that have been pulled from the ground or picked from trees that morning. Fruits, vegetables, meat, seafood, baked goods, pottery, crafts and plants are just a sample of what will be offered from local farmers at Sun Peaks over the next couple of months.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:22','2013-07-29 18:02:22',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(507,50.232,-121.581,NULL,'424 British Columbia 12, Lytton, BC V0K 1Z0, Canada','Two Rivers Farmers\' Market','tworiversfarmersmarket@live.ca','Thompson-Okanagan','250-455-0236','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/two-rivers-farmers-market','','','Friday, Summer, Fall: Market Season: Open from May 17-October 1, 2013. Come check out the home grown and made goodies at the Two Rivers Farmers\' Market in Lytton!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:22','2013-07-29 18:02:22',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(508,50.2752,-119.278,NULL,'3445 43 Ave, Vernon, BC V1T 8P5, Canada','Vernon Farmers\' Market','info@vernonfarmersmarket.ca','Thompson-Okanagan','250-351-5188','http://www.vernonfarmersmarket.ca','https://www.facebook.com/vernonfarmersmarket','https://twitter.com/VernonFarmerMkt','Mondays, Thursdays, Spring-Fall: Discover the diversity and uniqueness of the area at one of the very best Farmers’ Markets in the region. With over 200 local growers and artisans, we offer everything from fruit, vegetables, meat, seafood, crafts, art, gourmet foods, plants, flowers, gifts, and delicious baking. Buskers, live entertainment and children’s activities often add to the cheerful atmosphere. ',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:23','2013-07-29 18:02:23',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(509,50.2836,-119.269,NULL,'4900 27 St, VILLAGE GREEN MALL, Vernon, BC V1T 4Y9, Canada','Vernon Friday Night Farmers\' Market','mediashop@shaw.ca','Thompson-Okanagan','250-549-1588','http://www.vernonfarmersmarket.ca','https://www.facebook.com/vernonfarmersmarket','https://twitter.com/VernonFarmerMkt','Fridays, Summer-Fall: We have a nice, family friendly atmosphere, and a great setting to pick up your locally produced vegetables, fruit, baking and homemade goods. We are a smaller market with charm. The market is an excellent meeting place for family and friends.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:23','2013-07-29 18:02:23',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(510,54.6998,-127.051,NULL,'Trans-Canada Highway, Smithers, V0J, BC','Bulkley Valley Farmers\' Market','','Skeena-North Coast','250-846-9854','http://www.bvfarmersmarket.com/','','','Saturdays, Summer: The Bulkley Valley Farmers\' Market is a vibrant market located near downtown Smithers. Local music is featured every week. Many people come to visit and socialize, as well as to take advantage of localproducts. We have special days every year for kids and for seniors. Each fall and winter we move indoors to the gym at St. Joseph\'s School. Our indoor markets are held from 9am to noon.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:23','2013-09-16 00:25:09',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Smithers','CA','CA','BC','BC'),(511,49.1981,-123.997,NULL,'2296-2300 Bowen Road, Nanaimo, BC, V9T','Bowen Road Farmers\' Market','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-390-5199','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/bowen-road-farmers-market','','','Wednesdays, Summer: The Bowen Road Farmers’ Market is brand new! It was started by a group of people concerned about our ever quickly changing world, the loss of rurality, food production, food sustainability and the connection to the earth. Our market is fun and vibrant market. Weekly we feature musicians and of course a wide variety of friendly vendors and excellent products produced by organic growers who transport their food within a 50 mile radius. Come to the Bowen Road Farmers’ Market and meet the person who grows and produces the food you eat. See you soon!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:23','2013-09-16 00:48:11',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nanaimo','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(512,49.0879,-123.835,NULL,'2313 Yellow Point Road, Nanaimo, V9X 1W9, BC','Cedar Farmers\' Market','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-668-5783','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/cedar-farmers-market','','','Sundays, Summer: Take a Sunday drive out into the country, park in the fields of the Crow and Gate Neighbourhood Pub, feel grassy field below your feet and talk with the farmer that grows your food.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:23','2013-07-29 18:02:23',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(513,49.1597,-123.892,NULL,'Duke Point Ferry Terminal, Nanaimo, British Columbia','Duke Point Marketplace','rareessence@live.ca','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-324-2227','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/duke-point-marketplace','','','Monday-Sunday, Summer: All local handcrafts sold by the artisans',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:24','2013-09-16 00:54:15',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Nanaimo','CA','CA','BC','BC'),(514,48.7786,-123.708,NULL,'1 Kenneth St, Duncan, V9L 1W2, BC','Duncan Farmers\' Market','themarketmanager1@gmail.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-732-1723','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/duncan-farmers-market','','','Saturdays, Year Round: Welcome to our Farmers\' Market in the heart of the beautiful Cowichan Valley. The Valley the late James Barber aptly named \"Canada\'s Provence\". We can be found on Ingram Street and the Market Square in Downtown Duncan (look for the clock tower at City Hall). We invite you to come and spend your Saturdays at one of the largest farmers\' markets in B.C. With our \"you make it, you bake it, you grow it, you sell it\" philosophy - you will find a wide variety of local products to fulfill your \"100 mile diet\" needs.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:24','2013-09-16 00:53:35',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Duncan','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(515,49.4038,-123.509,NULL,'690-694 School Rd, Gibsons, V0N 1V9, BC','Gibsons Landing Sunday Market','','Vancouver Island-South Coast','','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/gibsons-landing-sunday-market','https://www.facebook.com/gibsons.landing.sunday.market','','Saturdays, Summer: We are the Gibsons Landing Sunday Market... come visit us Sundays 10am - 3pm (weather permitting) in Holland Park, May thru mid September.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:24','2013-07-29 18:02:24',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(516,48.4486,-123.498,NULL,'772 Goldstream Ave, Langford Center, Victoria,V9B 2X4, BC','Goldstream Station Market','info@goldstreamstationmarket.ca','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-507-5767','http://goldstreamstationmarket.ca','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Goldstream-Station-Market/198836553476740','https://twitter.com/Goldstream_Mkt','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: Walk, ride or cycle to Goldstream Station Market on Bryn Maur Road in downtown Langford! Bryn Maur Road, closed to traffic for the market on Saturdays from June to October, is modeled on a \"woonerf\" street design built more for pedestrian traffic than cars, and has a European flavour complemented by the Market. There are two coffee shops with patio seating right next door! This market is based on a \"you grow it, you make it, you bake it, you sell it\" philosophy. Farm fresh produce, arts and crafts, breads, preserves, music and more!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:25','2013-09-16 00:53:33',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Langford','CA','CA','BC','BC'),(517,48.4281,-123.365,NULL,'625-633 Pandora Ave, Victoria, BC V8W 1P6, Canada','James Bay Market','info@jamesbaymarket.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-381-5323','http://jamesbaymarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/jamesbaymarket','https://twitter.com/jamesbaymarket','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: You will be amazed at the variety of products available at the James Bay Market. Whether you’re a local in need of some fresh red peppers, or a visitor looking for that unique something from Victoria, we’ve got it. Handmade. Homemade, Homegrown. handmade arts and crafts live music coffee, cold drinks and home baked treats fresh flowers locally grown fruit, vegetables hot and cold snacks and more',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:25','2013-09-16 00:54:05',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'Victoria','CA','Canada','BC','British Columbia'),(518,49.2476,-124.073,NULL,'7113-7133 Lantzville Rd, Nanaimo D, BC V0R 2H0, Canada','Lantzville Farmers\' Market','lantzvillefarmersmarket@gmail.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-390-4487','http://lantzvillefarmersmarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/lantzvillefarmersmarketsociety','https://twitter.com/lantzvillefm','Sundays, Summer, Fall: Come out and enjoy music, and laughter. Meet your friends and neighbours over a cup of coffee or tea and a goodie. Browse the handicrafts on display, get a treat for Fido, and pick up fresh supper ingredients all in one location!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:25','2013-07-29 18:02:25',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(519,48.38,-123.536,NULL,'4450 Happy Valley Rd, Metchosin, BC V9C, Canada','Metchosin Farmers\' Market','metchosinfarmersmarket@gmail.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-478-4503','http://metchosinfarmersmarket.blog.com','','','Sundays, Summer, Fall: Take a leisurely drive to Metchosin country and browse through our market. You will find organic and naturally grown vegetables and fruit; Farm fresh eggs; jams, jellies and salsa, breads of every kind, cookies, muffins and much more! Pottery, jewellery, soap and bath items, essential oils and a variety of flowers. Cloth bags; Readings; books; garden pots and ornaments; plants and herbs (dried, fresh, and plants); veggie starters; tye-dyed accessories; tea cosies; hand knitted and crocheted items; and magnetic jewellery. Wander through our Pioneer Museum and then sit at a picnic table with a \"sausage in a bun\" made by our local Galloping Goose Company or listen to the live music. then saunter once more to each booth before heading out to a local beach or hiking trail (maps found on our bulletin board) before planning to come again to the Metchosin Farmers\' Market!',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:25','2013-07-29 18:02:25',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(520,48.4153,-123.349,NULL,'401 Moss St, Victoria, BC V8V 4N4, Canada ','Moss Street Community Market','info@mossstreetmarket.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-361-1747','http://www.mossstreetmarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/MossStMarket?ref=ts','https://twitter.com/MossStMarket','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: Who doesn\'t like to stroll through an open market sampling fresh prepared savory treats while relaxing with friends or family? To then realize that \"hey, I\'ve got room in the tummy for some dessert!\" Look around and discover a plethora of delightful baked goods, sweets, jams, etc, that will hit the spot nicely. The Moss St Market boasts a wonderful array of different food varieties and takes considerable pride in the quality, and regional proximity from which the food comes. The Market also has great live music and a free children\'s craft tent.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:25','2013-07-29 18:02:25',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(521,49.168,-123.936,NULL,'62-84 Front St, Nanaimo, BC V9R 7B5, Canada','Nanaimo Downtown Farmers\' Market','ndfms@shaw.ca','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-754-1998','http://www.nanaimofarmersmarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/NanaimoDowntownFarmersMarket','','Fridays, Summer, Fall: We are proud to say that we believe our market is one of the prettiest on the island. We have a large base of drop in vendors which keep our market ever changing. We enjoy watching the eagles fly overhead, the boats coming and going and the planes taking off every Friday. Our vendors always have a smile for our visitors.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:26','2013-07-29 18:02:26',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(522,48.6807,-123.458,NULL,'10990 W Saanich Rd, North Saanich, BC V8L 5P6, Canada ','North Saanich Farm Market','info@northsaanichfarmmarket.ca','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-656-1236','http://www.northsaanichfarmmarket.ca','https://www.facebook.com/pages/North-Saanich-Farm-Market/114647165219152?v=wall','https://twitter.com/nsfarmmarket','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: Seasonal produce, baked goods, eggs, flowers, honey, arts & crafts. Come meet local vendors who make, bake and grow what they sell. Live music every week.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:26','2013-07-29 18:02:26',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(523,48.4411,-123.339,NULL,'2827-2853 Belmont Ave, Victoria, BC V8R 4B2, Canada ','Oaklands Sunset Series: Farmers\' Markets & Community Events','alex@oaklandscommunitycentre.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-370-9101','http://www.oaklandscommunitycentre.com/content/oaklands-sunset-markets','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Oaklands-Community-Centre/113297908723315','https://twitter.com/oaklandsCC','Wednesdays, Summer: Open from June 12-August 28th, every second and fourth Wednesday: 4:30-8:30pm. Market Dates: June 12, June 26, July 10, July 24, Aug 14, Aug 28 2013. Oaklands Sunset Series invites you to join in on the fun this summer! Shop for fresh local produce, bakery items and local handmade arts and crafts. ',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:26','2013-07-29 18:02:26',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(524,48.5797,-123.433,NULL,'1528 Stellys Cross Rd, Saanichton, BC V8M 1S8, Canada','Peninsula Country Market','peninsulacountrymarket@gmail.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-216-0521','http://www.peninsulacountrymarket.ca','https://www.facebook.com/PeninsulaCountryMarket','','Saturdays, Summer, Fall: This vibrant open-air market has more than 50 vendors offering farm fresh products, jams and jellies, honey, homemade bread, cut flowers, assorted meats, organic produce and a fine selection of arts and crafts. Enjoy a country morning among friends. Live music, hot coffee, great munchies and a kid\'s korral.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:26','2013-07-29 18:02:26',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(525,50.0333,-125.274,NULL,'2000-2034 Island Hwy, Campbell River, BC V9W 3M8, Canada','Pier Street Farmers\' Market','market@pierstreet.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-203-1399','http://www.pierstreet.com','','','Sundays, Summer, Fall: CANADIAN GEOGRAPHIC ‘SUMMER TRAVEL 2009 lists our market at the top of their ‘TOP TEN’ list !!! For ALL OF CANADA !!! Find out why by coming down for a visit. Are you one of the Campbell Riverites who are always meaning to come down, but just never seem to make it? Why not this weekend?',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:26','2013-07-29 18:02:26',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(526,49.234,-124.806,NULL,'3027 4 Ave, Port Alberni, BC V9Y 2B8, Canada','Port Alberni Farmers\' Market','vickilee@telus.net','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250-723-7472','http://www.portalbernifarmersmarket.com','','','Saturdays, Year Round: The Port Alberni Farmers\' Market is a traditional farmers market promoting locally grown produce and locally made products from the Alberni Clayquot Regional District. The Market is open year round and provides a wide assortment of meats, vegetables,fruits and fresh free range eggs. Located at the foot of Argyle Street in the center of the picturesque Harbour Quay, the Market provides a meeting place for old and new friends. Locals and tourists alike can always find a friendly conversation and lots of smiling faces amongst the hustle and bustle that is Market Day.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:27','2013-07-29 18:02:27',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(527,49.844,-124.483,NULL,'4335-4639 McLeod Rd, Powell River B, BC V8A, Canada','Powell River\'s Open Air Farmers\' Market','jesseblack@gmail.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','604-344-0021','http://met.bcfarmersmarket.org/market/powell-rivers-open-air-farmers-market','https://www.facebook.com/openairfarmersmarket','','Saturday, Sunday, Spring-Fall: The market is an old-fashioned, country-style market selling fresh, locally grown produce, bedding plants, home-baking, honey, soap, woodcrafts, jewelery, and a variety of original items hand-crafted by local artisans.  Livestock is present on occasion for sale and display. Produce is grown without pesticides or herbicides, the market supports sustainable practices. Information on local food and farming issues is available. ',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:27','2013-07-29 18:02:27',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(528,49.3483,-124.441,NULL,'632-644 Memorial Ave, Qualicum Beach, BC V9K 1P6, Canada','Qualicum Beach Farmers\' Market','qbfmmanager@gmail.com','Vancouver Island-South Coast','250 248-8005','http://www.qbfarmersmarket.com','https://www.facebook.com/pages/Qualicum-Beach-Farmers-Market/247685375267830','https://twitter.com/qbfarmersmarket','Saturday, Spring to October: Located in the heart of the beautiful village of Qualicum Beach, the Farmers\' Market specializes in fresh produce, meat, seafood, and value added products.',1,'2013-07-29 18:02:27','2013-07-29 18:02:27',13,'Location',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(529,48.8521,-123.5,NULL,'149 Fulford Ganges Rd, Salt Spring Island, BC V